The following commands are available to you as a member of the Drow
race guild of Undraeth, within Kalad:
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
dhelp.....This menu.
dlanguage.A brief glossary of Drow words.
dtitles...A list of all the titles of the Drow guild.
dlist.....Call on the power of Lolth to see which other Drow are on.
dsay......Speak in the ancient tongue of the Drow.
ds........Sneer something at someone.
dsight....Use your Lolth-given power to see in the darkness.
dsmile....Smile as only a drow could.
dbow......Bow with incredible grace and ease.
dcurtsey..Curtsey with feline grace and poise.
drespect..Show respect to someone you deem worthy.
dsneer....Sneer in contempt of the surface dwellers.
dmalice...Glare at someone maliciously.
danger....Look at someone with intense, burning anger.
dstoic....Look at someone without emotion.
dglare....Glare at someone coldly and haughtily.
doath.....Declare an oath to Lolth and Undraeth.
ddeath....Promise someone a slow and painful death.
dlaugh....Laugh at someone with malicious glee.
dlust.....Gaze at someone lustfully.
dpain.....Cringe in pain at something.
dsign.....Relate a message via the Drow sign language.
dgreet....Greet someone in the manner of the Drow.
kill......Scream out a battle-cry as you attack someone.
drude.....Point at someone and convey something rude.
dsnarl....Clench your jaw and curl your lip in a feral snarl.
dhowl.....Throw your head back and let out a howl of triumph.
dcurse....Curse bitterly in drowish.
dnarrow...Regard someone with scrutiny. (Try 'dnarrow <subject> <adv>')
dgaze.....Level your gaze at someone.
droar.....Roar at someone with uncontained wrath.
dwatch....Watch someone out of the corner of your eye.
dgrimace..Grimace in frustration and spit out a phrase. ('dgrimace Die!')
dfare.....Bid someone farewell.
dpray.....Whisper a silent prayer to Lolth.
dscream...Let loose a scream of unbridled rage.
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
* Note: After performing certain emotes, said emotes will show up in
        your description.
* Note: To pass by the gate guarding the entrance to Undraeth, simply
        say (using 'dsay') open and close while at the gate, and the
        invisible guardians shall do your bidding.
